1.  install bind9
(1) sudo apt-get install bind9
(2) sudo dpkg -L bind9
(3) netstat -tunlp | grep 53

2.  named.conf includes the following files:
(1) /etc/bind/named.conf.options
(2) /etc/bind/named.conf.default-zone
(3) /etc/bind/named.conf.local

3. start bind9 service and check status
sudo /etc/init.d/bind9 restart
vi /var/log/sysconfig

4.  zone files
directory: /var/cache/bind
